
                                              ==================
                                              SPRING ANNOTATIONS
                                              ==================                                      


Annotations==> represents metadata
=> Annotations introduced in java 1.5v

=> Annotations are alternate for xml configuration.
=> In SpringFramework we have several annotations.

1.@Configuration: To represent java class as Configuration class.
2.@ComponentScan: To identify springBean classes available in the project based on "basePackageName".
3.@Component: To represent java class in spring bean.
4.@Service: To represent java class in spring bean.(Bussiness layer classes)
5.@Repository: To represent java class in spring bean.(Persistance layer classes )
6.@Scope: To represent bean scope 
8.@Autowired: To perform dependency injection
9.Qualifier: to perform autowiring based on byName.
10.@Primary: To represent primary bean for autowiring.
11.@Bean: To call the method which returns bean object.

